   <h1>Baked Chicken Breast</h1> 
   <img src="https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/3bpOHgCnhxSvX9m5RUlF2uwZL90=/750x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc():format(webp)/2267790-three-ingredient-baked-chicken-breasts-naples34102-1x1-1-016207151c2d47bd926ffa56d11dc6ef.jpg">
   <h2>Description</h2>
        <p>An easy 3-ingredient recipe which will give you the best baked chicken breasts</p>
    <h3>Ingredients</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>1/4 Cup butter, melted</li>
            <li>1 Teaspoon salt</li>
            <li>4 SKinless chicken breasts</li>
        </ul>
    <h3>Steps:</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly butter a baking dish.</li>
            <li>Stir together melted butter and salt in a bowl</li>
            <li>Arrange chicken in the prepared baking dish. Brush butter mixture onto chicken until thoroughly coated, pouring any extra over chicken.</li>
            <li>Bake in the preheated oven until no longer pink in the center and juices run clear, 30 to 45 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).</li>
        </ol>
